claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table listing trade names and manufacturers of quadrivalent influenza vaccines and their dose volumes (µg HA per vaccine virus) for children aged 6 through 35 months, including Afluria Quadrivalent (Seqirus), Fluarix Quadrivalent (GlaxoSmithKline), Flucelvax Quadrivalent (Seqirus), FluLaval Quadrivalent (GlaxoSmithKline), and Fluzone Quadrivalent (Sanofi Pasteur) with doses of 7.5 µg or 15 µg of HA per strain. The table does not include any information about Flublok or its HA content, so it does not support the claim. Note: The image is clear and shows pediatric dosing for other vaccines; absence of Flublok in this table limits any evaluation of its HA content.
